[This ledger, written in fine strokes by a precise hand, has a marker set towards the back of its pages.  You turn to the page, where an entry reads:

"I have found myself thinking a great deal of my mother in the last few days.  I believe that little homeless girl I saw in the Market District the other day brought this particular case of nostalgia upon me.  She was sitting beside one of the merchant stands, reciting an old poem mother used to tease my sister with...

The boy to my right has nine cakes,
The one on my left has only one,
I'm so hungry I've got the shakes,
But boys don't share, and I have none...

A silly little thing, really, but it used to make me smile when I was a lad.  Come to think of it, this little poem gives me an idea for arranging the warding runes on the Control Stone.  Maybe now I won't forget the combination so often...

I believe I'll do that right now.  Captain Anagril is escorting those visiting sorcerers from the south in as I write, so I'll need to be quick about it..."

This is the last entry in the ledger, for it seems Zhiram never had an opportunity to write more.]

Sitting atop this altar is the Control Stone of Ghaarak, a powerful orb of magical energies crafted by the Imperial sorcerers of the city.  This stone is used to activate and deactivate the magical wards guarding the Imperial District gates, in times of emergency, and is also used to control the constructs which aid in day to day Imperial labor.
A searing shaft of golden light descends from some unseen place above.
Emperor Rakha's stony gaze bears down on you.

Emperor Rakha's stony gaze bears down on you.
A small drawer extends beneath the gleaming tabletop. It probably doubles as a desk when there's the need.

Magistrate Okaris,

It has come to my attention that your child will soon participate in the final tests to graduate the Imperial Academy.  I know you must be quite proud to see your offspring reach such a prestigious achievement, and we of Zhantara extend our blessings to your family.

I would like to take this chance to ask what future you foresee for your child.  I know you and I have often discussed the possibility of further training amongst the ranks of the ShadowGuard, and I was curious as to whether you have given this proposal any further thought.

I have consulted Emperor Rakha regarding this matter, and He feels such a path would be most beneficial to all involved.  The decision lies with you, of course, but please do give this matter some thought.  

On other matters, I will be visiting your city of Ghaarak soon, and I am quite interested in investigating this gem your men recently uncovered.  Your recent letters have suggested that you are frightened of its power, and rightfully so.  If this thing is truly a relic of the Golden Age, its might is surely greater than we mortals of this age could fathom.  

As you know, Emperor Rakha has taken a great interest in any ancient relics of late, and He wishes to discover more of your finding.  Please prepare a full report for my coming, and we will discuss this matter further in person.

Your friend,

Overlord Vhorkas, High Commander of Zhantara

[This letter, found amidst the belongings of Chancellor Varhun of Ghaarak, reads:

"Chancellor, I write in response to your plea for aid with your current... dilemma...  It seems both you and I have a great desire to see an end to the rule of Magistrate Okaris, a thorn in both our sides.  I have devised a plan in which we may rid ourselves of the Magistrate once and for all, one which we will discuss in further detail upon my arrival.  Should you hear of an appearance by a prophet, garbed in red, be prepared to take matters into your own hands immediately.

Beyond that, you may choose how else to serve your own advancement in the Imperial ranks.  Just be certain to use discretion, as it would not do for our plans to be revealed prematurely.

Remember, should the prophet in red appear, it is imperative that Okaris does not live to see the next dawn.  If you serve us well, we may be able to find other purposes to which we can apply your skills..."

The letter is unsigned.]
Bound in iron and with a heavy lock, this heavy chest was obviously meant to protect something of value.

The Control Stone is a device unlike any other ever created here in Ghaarak. Its tremendous power has been utilized for many extraordinary purposes. The grandest of these achievements is certainly the impervious shield we can summon over the district gates in the unlikely event we ever come under attack. In addition, the stone has been used extensively for the purpose of animating magical constructs to aid in menial tasks of labor, allowing our Imperial citizens ample time to pursue more fitting pursuits.

Activation of the Control Stone is quite simple. The simple arcane phrase, "Milak Navok", is all that is needed to summon forth the stone's power, though of course we have placed runes of warding to prevent any improper use. High Sorcerer Zhiram has been placed in charge of the Control Stone's usage, so should you need to utilize its abilities, please speak with him. Only he can give you the proper rune combination to pass through its protections, and command the power of the stone.

Be wary of tampering with the stone in any unlawful fashion. The sorceries at work within are quite potent, and if unleashed, could prove quite destructive and dangerous.
